6:
Whew! That was way easier than 
I thought!
9:
Dude, I can't believe Grampa agreed 
to resign! Now I'm the chief, all that's 
left is for me to sign the peace treaty!
12:
I'm amazed you managed to 
convince him.
15:
Heh. You know what they say, bro. 
There sure is strength in numbers!
20:
The effort spent collecting signatures 
for the petition paid off.
25:
I guess all's well that ends well... Even if
some were—uh—LESS thrilled to sign 
than others.
30:
Hey, don't look at me. I just stood 
there while Claw did the "sweet 
talking."
36:
At any rate, the petition served its 
purpose. Now we need only return to 
the cas—
41:
What was that clang? 
Sounds like a fight!
45: I can smell blood. Let's press on!
49:
You! 
We've got you cornered, now!
57: Hey, you're that guy we fought!
74:
Klaus the Dire... To think, you were still
alive!
76:
Nimbus, I shall deal with him! Stand 
back!
79: Looks like he's here for me, though.
81: The dire wolves don't act on their own!
82:
If he is after your life, it is at the will of 
his contractor—the king!
83:
What in the bloody hell was that old 
fool thinking? To order an 
assassination NOW of all times! 
Leave this mess to me, Nimbus.
95:
Who do you think murdered your 
father? My pack, the dire wolves! 
Have you no honor?!
98: So you DO know how to talk.
100:
Here I was thinkin' you just wag your 
tail and do whatever the king tells 
you!
105:
You aren't even old enough to've killed 
King Whitetail. Don't get ahead of 
yourself!
108: Albert, we'll take him with us for now.
109:
You guys are so close to makin' the 
peace treaty happen. If word of an 
assassination attempt got out, it'd 
just complicate everything.
112:
It would indeed, but... 
Are you sure?
133:
Welcome to Starview Village. 
I am its Keeper, Stella.
136:
You—you were with Whitetail. 
Why are you here?
139:
I have a message for you from
Nimbus. 
I kicked your ass into next week, so be 
a good boy and stay in bed.
140:
Your king called off the assassination 
with his tail between his legs, but if 
you still wanna fight, suit yourself.
144:
There is no one here to issue you 
orders or contracts. As Nimbus said, 
please "suit yourself" and enjoy your 
stay.
148:
But...
But WHY would you... I don't 
understand.
